18/02/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Opposition leaders announced on Sunday (February 17th) they are ready to form a new government if the current one falls in a coming vote of no-confidence. At a joint press conference, leaders of the Citizens for the European Development of Bulgaria, the Union of Democratic Forces, Bulgarian New Democracy, Attack, Democrats for a Strong Bulgaria, Order, Law and Justice, VMRO-BND, the Agrarian National Union and independent lawmaker Lachezar Ivanov expressed their joint position against the "corrupt" government of the Bulgarian Socialist Party, the National Movement for Stability and Progress, and the Movement for Rights and Freedom. The vote, scheduled for Friday, is expected to fail. (Darik, BNR, Netinfo - 17/02/08)
